<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1822,2027]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,474,1858,1883]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" reason="1">Diagnostic description.</emphasis>
Body shape slender. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[712,1319,1858,1883]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Head lateral cephalic lobe large, narrowly rounded</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Antenna 1 peduncular article 1 without posterodistal spine; accessory flagellum article 1 short; flagellum without callynophore in female</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[407,522,1930,1955]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Mandible</emphasis>
with accessory setal row present on both sides; left lamina dentata absent; 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">palp attached slightly distally</emphasis>
; palp article 2 broad, article 3 not distally tapered, with margins convex or subparallel. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,873,2002,2027]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Maxilla 1 outer plate setal-teeth smooth or with weak cusps</emphasis>
; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[890,1229,2002,2026]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">palp well developed, slender</emphasis>
, 1-articulate or 2-
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,151,428]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
articulate. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[270,399,151,176]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Maxilliped</emphasis>
inner plate small; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[611,810,152,176]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">outer plate large</emphasis>
; palp 4-articulate, article 4 large. Gnathopod 1 ischium smaller than propodus; corner of palm with simple robust seta or without robust seta. Gnathopod 2 palm transverse or acute. Epimeron 3 posteroventral corner broadly rounded or subquadrate. Uropod 3 biramous.
</paragraph>
